A brief background on the company is provided below to answer the questions 
raised:

Genesys International Corporation Limited is an Indian company. It was listed 
on Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) on Monday June 6, 2000 and is traded on the B2 
group on the  (BSE) under ticker code 6109.  We have purchased 190,000 shares 
at Rs. 225 per share (total of Rs. 42.75 million). (The site for the BSE is 
www.bseindia.com.)

1) The shares are owned by Enron Distribution Ventures MHC Limited (Mauritius 
Based). The physical share certificates are with Enron India in a vault in 
a     bank
2) There is no lock up restriction on the shares purchased by us and we are 
free to sell these shares.
3) I am not clear on the materal non-public information and who would need to 
give the certification. Could you clarify where the requirement for the 
certification arises, and send me a copy of the form of the certificate.
4) We would need a broker in India who is authorised to deal on the BSE to 
execute the transactions, A person acting on behalf of Enron Distribution 
Ventures  MHC Limited Mauritius would need to enter into the relevant 
agreements and authorisations
5) I do not think that Goldman Sachs would be able to sell these shares on 
our behalf on the BSE as we would need a broker here in India to execute the 
deal

Under Indian Regulations, the proceeds from the sale of shares on behalf of 
the foriegn company needs to be deposited in a rupee bank account and then 
can be onward remitted to Enron Distribution Ventures MHC Limited account. 
The bank has the responsibility of carrying out the due diligence for 
adherence to the current Reserve Baank of India rules regarding sale of 
shares in the Indian Market by an overseas company.

I hope that I have provided the relevant information required. In addition, I 
have enclosed a copy of the DASH for your reference.

Donna : Would request you to advise us on how to proceed further on this one.




Regards







