Hi Rajesh,

Further to your discussion with Hari regarding an OCB account, please find 
below the list of documents required to open an  account with Deutsche Bank.

   Memorandum and Articles of Association
   Certificate of Incorporation
   Tax Residence Certificate
   Offshore Certificate
   Power of Attorney
   Board Resolution appointing DB as custodians for security and cash accounts
   Authorised Signatory list
   Account opening forms duly signed with Copies of Passport and Photographs.
   RPC Application form (The company seal is required to be endorsed on this 
form)
   OAC certificate ( Overseas Auditors Certificate)

Also the custody agreement, fee schedule and a service level agreement need 
to be executed. A draft copy of the custody agreemnet and the POA is attached 
for your reference.

Custody Agreement             Power of Attorney


Please revert in case you have any questions

thanks & kind regards, abby

